⭐ Using AWS S3 to Upload Files and Manage Access
➤ Step 1: Open the S3 Service

• Log in to the AWS Management Console
• Open S3 from the list of services

➤ Step 2: Create or Select a Bucket

• Choose an existing bucket or click Create Bucket
• Keep default settings or choose a region

➤ Step 3: Upload Two Files

• Open the bucket
• Click Upload
• Add two files from the system
• Click Upload to complete

➤ Step 4: Set One File to Public

• Select the first file
• Click Actions → Make Public (or Permissions → Public access)
• Confirm the setting
• A public link will be generated automatically

➤ Step 5: Keep One File Private

• Select the second file
• Ensure that “Block Public Access” remains enabled
• This file stays private and cannot be accessed publicly

➤ Step 6: Generate a Pre-Signed URL (for Private File)

• Select the private file
• Click Actions → Share with a pre-signed URL
• Choose expiration time (e.g., 1 hour)
• Copy the generated pre-signed URL

➤ Step 7: Record the Details in Lab Notebook

• Paste the following into your lab record:
– Bucket Name
– Public File Link
– Private File Pre-Signed URL
– Upload steps
– Access settings
